{"key":"post-19746378","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>19746378</id>\n<content>The bottom line is if anyone says to never mist, consider them an idiot and ignore the bad advice.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A major pinning trigger is loss of moisture from the substrate after full colonization.&amp;nbsp; Your substrate is &lt;i&gt;supposed&lt;/i&gt; to slightly dry out, and then you mist to replace that moisture.&amp;nbsp; Never saturate your substrate and never allow it to fully dry out.&amp;nbsp; Especially never seal up a substrate where it can't get rid of excess moisture and metabolic gasses.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>19746410</next>\n<prev>19746286</prev>\n<first>19746214</first>\n<last>19746410</last>\n<when>1395792228</when>\n<utime>03/26/14 03:03 AM</utime>\n</post>"}